               <p>JAMES DARVILL. I live at <placeName id="t18260914-227-crimeloc1299">Uxbridge</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-227-crimeloc1299" type="placeName" value="Uxbridge"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-227-crimeloc1299" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-227-off1297 t18260914-227-crimeloc1299"></join>; I am a <rs id="t18260914-227-viclabel1300" type="occupation">shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-227-victim1284 t18260914-227-viclabel1300"></join>. On Saturday, the 5th of August, I missed a pair of shoes about five o'clock, which I had given to the prisoner on the Friday morning, to make for me - he worked in my house; he came to work about seven o'clock on Saturday morning; I told him they were missing; he said, he had left them under his seat the night before; I said, I was determined to find out who stole them, as I had lost a watch and some other articles - he said, he he knew nothing about the shoes; and I might as well say, he stole the watch - I wished him to stop while I went to get somebody.</p>
               <p>
            
